# Engineering standards (org)

## Ask when unclear

Before non-trivial work: ask **1–2 focused questions** (use AskQuestion when options are concrete). Do not guess on scope, persistence, or auth. Proceed without blocking for obvious fixes or explicit instructions.

## Verify before done

Before claiming work is complete, fixed, or ready to commit/PR:

- Run the project's verification commands (tests, build, lint).
- Confirm output — evidence before assertions.

## Code changes

- Minimal scope — smallest correct diff.
- Match existing conventions in the repo.
- Useful tests only — no trivial or CSS-class-only assertions.
- Comments only for non-obvious logic.

## Secrets

Never commit secrets, tokens, or credential material.
